{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "14", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "11", "M": "15", "S": "30"}}, "news": [{"title": "Beyond buildings: How architects are shaping sustainability and policy today", "para": "Architects now contribute significantly to India's development and urban planning.  Their interdisciplinary knowledge enhances their influence on decision-making processes.  Growing public demand for quality spaces expands the architect's professional scope.  Sustainability and policy development are key areas where architects offer expertise.  This evolving role positions architecture to shape India's future settlements.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/blog/architects-driving-sustainable-urban-development-and-policy-in-india/132387342?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-776130/132387342.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "architects-driving-sustainable-urban-development-and-policy-in-india"}, {"title": "As India's energy revolution accelerates, real estate stands to gain", "para": "Energy access is shifting from security to national sovereignty for nations. Real estate infrastructure converts energy potential into sustained economic value for India. Industrial parks and renewable energy facilities create economic epicenters and ecosystems. India's policy architecture supports energy ambition and infrastructure execution. Real estate is the ground for India's energy sovereignty and global standing.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/blog/indias-energy-revolution-a-boon-for-real-estate-development/132387107?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1398988/132387107.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "indias-energy-revolution-a-boon-for-real-estate-development"}, {"title": "Rajasthan: 86 colonies plan mahapanchayat over pending land titles", "para": "Residents of 86 colonies in Sanganer and Bagru are demanding land titles.  These families established their homes decades ago through cooperative societies.  They warn of boycotting local body elections if demands are unmet.  A mahapanchayat and public movement are planned if no decision occurs.  The Niyaman Hetu Sangharsh Samiti leads this ongoing community effort.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/rajasthan-colonies-threaten-election-boycott-over-land-title-issues/132386111?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1747617/132386111.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}